Although 55% of the students did not experience any stress from peers during the
COVID-19 lockdown, high competition among peers turned out to be the most commonly cited
peer stressor (Table 3). Even though the lockdown resulted in increased screen time for students
due to the introduction of online classes and a more significant role of social media, the statistics
reveal cyber stress and cyberbullying affected a small proportion of students. 25.9% (57) of the
respondents felt that the stress from peers affected them negatively in terms of mental health and
well-being. The 5-point Likert scale analysis (Table 4) disclosed that most students did not
experience any change in stress due to peers during the lockdown.
